7 And I turned to the sea of all wisdom;
8 I said: "What does this one say? and what does
9 that other fire answer? and who are those who made it?".

25 My guide descended into the boat,
26 and then made me enter after him;
27 and only when I was inside did it seem laden.

34 And I to him: "If I come, I do not stay;
35 but who are you, who have become so filthy?".
36 He replied: "See that I am one who weeps".

37 And I to him: "With weeping and with mourning,
38 accursed spirit, you remain;
39 for I know you, even though you are all filthy".

40 Then he stretched out both hands to the boat;
41 because of which the wary master pushed him away,
42 saying: "Away with you there with the other dogs!".

43 Then he put his arms around my neck;
44 he kissed my face and said: "Disdainful soul,
45 blessed is she who became pregnant with you!

46 That was a proud person in the world;
47 there is no goodness that adorns his memory:
48 thus his shade is furious here.

61 All were shouting: "At Filippo Argenti!";
62 and the bizarre Florentine spirit
63 was turning on himself with his teeth.

64 There we left him, and I will say no more of him;
65 but a sound of grief struck my ears,
66 so that I opened my intent eyes wide.

100 do not leave me", I said, "so undone;
101 and if passing further is denied to us,
102 let us find our steps together quickly".

112 I could not hear what he said to them;
113 but he did not stay there with them long,
114 for each one rushed back inside, vying with the others.

124 This insolence of theirs is not new;
125 for they already used it at a less secret gate,
126 which is still found without a lock.
